rtl / resettasklabel          Resets task labels to default values

   Format:
      ;rtl <task>             Resets <task>'s list of labels to default values
      ;rtl                    Resets all task labels to default values

   Notes:
      Axmud tasks have formal names like 'status_task' and 'locator_task'. Task
         labels are a convenient way of referring to tasks without having to
         type the whole name. For example, the Status task has the task labels
         'stat' and 'status' by default.
      Using ';resettasklabel' will mean that only Axmud's built-in tasks will
         have task labels.

   User commands:
      rtl / resettl / resetlabel / resettasklabel
